column29: Seeds of naturally growing Arabidopsis thaliana plants were collected in the plot Babchin (Polesye State Radioecological Reserve, Gomel Region, Republic of Belarus, 46.47 km from the Chernobyl nuclear power plant, replication 1) in June 2019. Seeds were planted for germination (exposure time - 13 days) for further extraction of total RNA. To identify a presumable radioadaptation of A. thaliana populations from plots with different levels of radioactive contamination, the seeds were exposed to acute -radiation at a dose of 150 Gy using irradiation facility GUR-120 (Russian Institute of Radiology and Agroecology, Obninsk, Russian Federation)
